Saruman&#39;s Snows x3<br />
<!--57-->Worry x2  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Basically you want to bid zero all the time to make sure you get out your sites 2 and 3, because they help you out quite a bit. On the occasions that you go first your site 1 doesn&#39;t hurt you too much as you have you other companions to play. If you get the Sting out early use it to scout the opponents hand and decide whether or not to move 2 sites at a time. With the Hobbits, you don&#39;t need to win many skirmishes, just survive till the start of the next turn so you can heal with the allies.<br />
<br />
As for the Shadow side of this deck, it&#39;s mostly beatdown in nature. The reason for the Soldiers and Messengers is a lot of the time I found I had that extra 2 twilight that I couldn&#39;t spend on anything in my hand, so I threw in some cheaper guys. A lot of the time they&#39;ll just draw away the directed archery fire from my stronger minions just so I can&#39;t pile them up on Frodo. The Messengers also work great with the snows out, nothing like dropping a Fighter, exerting him for the snows then dropping 2 Messengers and watching the other guy cringe. The Worries also work great with the snows, cause most of the time you&#39;ll be winning skirmishes. <br />
<br />
The sites are easy enough to figure out. 1 through 3 help the Fellowship, while the rest work better for my Shadow. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
